"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-iga-swiatek-french-open-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Two matches after the longest French Open match of her career, Iga Swiatek played her shortest one.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 99, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 63, \"end\": 66, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 9.900976070574216e-13, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swiatek dispatched 41st-ranked Anastasia Potapova 6-0, 6-0 - a double bagel in tennis terminology - in 40 minutes to reach a fifth consecutive French Open quarterfinal.\", \"from\": 101, \"to\": 269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was just really focused and really in the zone,\\\" Swiatek said.\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 336, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wasn't looking at the score, so I just continued playing my game and working on the stuff I wanted to work on.\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yeah, it went pretty quickly, pretty weird.\\\"\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She next gets fifth-seeded Czech Marketa Vondrousova, the Wimbledon champion.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 524, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999197269316366, \"rank\": 7.674182670726046e-05, \"text\": \"Czech\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"3 seed Coco Gauff and No.\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coco Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"8 Ons Jabeur also advanced Sunday to meet in the quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FRENCH OPEN DRAWS:Men|Women|Broadcast Schedule  Swiatek won 48 of the 58 points in Sunday's match, the second 6-0, 6-0 win of her French Open career.\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is 32-2 at Roland Garros since her 2019 debut.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before Sunday, her shortest French Open match was a 6-1, 6-0 loss to Simona Halep in 2019 in 45 minutes,according to Tennis Abstract.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 941, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simona_Halep\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simona Halep\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simona_Halep\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simona_Halep\"}, {\"begin\": 989, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.706109736468109e-16, \"text\": \"Tennis\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her longest match came this year in the second round, a 7-6 (1), 1-6, 7-5 win over fellow four-time major champ Naomi Osaka in 2 hours, 57 minutes.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1119, \"end\": 1130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naomi_Osaka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Naomi Osaka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naomi_Osaka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naomi_Osaka\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swiatek is three match wins from becoming the fourth and youngest woman in the professional era (since 1968) to win four French Open singles titles.\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's draw, No.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"3 seed Carlos Alcaraz and No.\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"9 seed Stefanos Tsitsipas advanced to play each other in the quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Tsitsipas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Tsitsipas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Tsitsipas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Tsitsipas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Open continues later Sunday with live coverage at 12 p.m.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET on NBC, NBCSports.com, the NBC Sports app andPeacock.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1511, \"end\": 1514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9805746448171265, \"rank\": 0.016461140349917736, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1516, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCSports.com\", \"types\": [], \"